replies.bodyText:
An assert statement always distracts a bit

Thats a bit subjective :) I think asserts can do a great job in communicating intend (even though the present case is not a particularly good example for this).

it is no if+throw because even if there is a bug we'll never know with assert, because in production it is disabled and in tests it does not happen

Yes and like I said I did not add the assert because its supposed to throw anything (we check wether or not the profile exists in checkConsistency() already.

So for higher level code where speed does not matter I would always use an if statement

I did not decide to use assert for performance reasons here. Performing a single if is probably very rarely a performance issue (and especially not here).
What do you prefer?
// option 1:
Profile profile = profiles.get(profileName);
// profile cannot be null because we checked already
profile.doSth();

// option2
Profile profile = profiles.get(profile);
profile.doSth();

// option3
Profile profile = profiles.get(profile);
assert profile != null : "profile does not exist even though this should have been checked already";
profile.doSth();
Here, I am happy with any of the options, but I would not agree if we tried to never use assert whatsoever. Like I said this is not a particular good/important use-case here.

